  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vanuatu Tropical Cyclone Pam 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As Tropical Cyclone Pam continues to make way in the South Pacific Ocean towards New Zealand after battering Vanuatu on Friday 13 March 205 with Category V strength a gloomy picture of its impact has begun to emerge. What is turning out to be one of the worst cyclones to affect the Pacific in recent history has left massive humanitarian needs across inhabited islands of Vanuatu. Described as the strongest storm to make landfall since Typhoon Haiyan hit the Philippines in November 2013 Pam flattened homes uprooted trees and caused considerable damage even on sturdy buildings such as schools and the city s main hospital. Based on the sheer size of the storm its ferocity and the track it took right over inhabited islands it is expected that there has been extreme destruction with thousands of people left without shelter and stripped of their source of livelihoods.</narrative>
  </description>
